{"primaryContentSections":[{"kind":"declarations","declarations":[{"platforms":["macOS"],"languages":["swift"],"tokens":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"func"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"childWatchSourceNew","kind":"identifier"},{"text":"(","kind":"text"},{"kind":"externalParam","text":"pid"},{"text":": ","kind":"text"},{"kind":"typeIdentifier","preciseIdentifier":"c:@T@GPid","text":"GPid"},{"text":") -> ","kind":"text"},{"text":"SourceRef","preciseIdentifier":"s:4GLib9SourceRefV","identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/SourceRef","kind":"typeIdentifier"},{"text":"!","kind":"text"}]}]},{"kind":"content","content":[{"type":"heading","level":2,"anchor":"discussion","text":"Discussion"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"The source will not initially be associated with any"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"[struct","type":"text"},{"isActive":true,"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/MainContext"},{"text":"] and must be added to one with","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"[method","type":"text"},{"code":"GLib.Source.attach","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":"] before it will be executed."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"Note that child watch sources can only be used in conjunction with","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"g_spawn..."},{"type":"text","text":" when the [flags"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"GLib.SpawnFlags.DO_NOT_REAP_CHILD"},{"type":"text","text":"] flag is used."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Note that on platforms where [type"},{"type":"reference","isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/Pid"},{"text":"] must be explicitly closed","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"(see [func"},{"code":"GLib.spawn_close_pid","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":"]) "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"pid"},{"text":" must not be closed while the","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"source is still active. Typically, you will want to call"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"[func","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"GLib.spawn_close_pid"},{"text":"] in the callback function for the source.","type":"text"}]},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"On POSIX platforms, the following restrictions apply to this API","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"due to limitations in POSIX process interfaces:","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"items":[{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"codeVoice","code":"pid"},{"text":" must be a child of this process.","type":"text"}]}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"code":"pid","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" must be positive."}]}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"The application must not call "},{"isActive":true,"type":"reference","identifier":"man:waitpid(1)"},{"text":" with a","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"non-positive first argument, for instance in another thread."}]}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"text":"The application must not wait for ","type":"text"},{"code":"pid","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" to exit by any other","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"mechanism, including ","type":"text"},{"code":"waitpid(pid, ...)","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" or a second child-watch"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"source for the same "},{"code":"pid","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":".","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"text":"The application must not ignore ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"SIGCHLD"},{"type":"text","text":"."}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"text":"Before 2.78, the application could not send a signal (","type":"text"},{"type":"reference","identifier":"man:kill(2)","isActive":true},{"text":") to the","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"watched ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"pid"},{"type":"text","text":" in a race free manner. Since 2.78, you can do that while the"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"associated [struct"},{"isActive":true,"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/MainContext"},{"type":"text","text":"] is acquired."}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Before 2.78, even after destroying the [struct","type":"text"},{"isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/Source","type":"reference"},{"text":"], you could not","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"be sure that "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"pid"},{"type":"text","text":" wasn’t already reaped. Hence, it was also not"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"safe to "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"kill()"},{"type":"text","text":" or "},{"code":"waitpid()","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" on the process ID after the child watch","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"source was gone. Destroying the source before it fired made it","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"impossible to reliably reap the process."}]}]}],"type":"unorderedList"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"If any of those conditions are not met, this and related APIs will"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"not work correctly. This can often be diagnosed via a GLib warning","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"stating that "},{"code":"ECHILD","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" was received by "},{"code":"waitpid()","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":".","type":"text"}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Calling "},{"type":"reference","identifier":"man:waitpid(2)","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":" for specific processes other 